==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sanguineous
<hw>San*guin"e*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>sanguineus</ets>. See <er>Sanguine</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Abounding with blood; sanguine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to blood; bloody; constituting
blood.</def> <rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Blood-red; crimson.</def>
<rj><au>Keats.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>sanguinity</ent>⟦br⟧
